description:
&lt;p&gt;Applications are invited for a new consultant post in General Surgery. The successful candidate will be a full time appointment in General &amp; Colorectal Surgery. The candidate will be expected to integrate within the team of existing consultants in order to provide a complete General Surgery service. He/she will be expected to have a sub specialty interest in Colorectal Surgery of which expertise in management of disorders of the pelvic floor would be desirable.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In addition to the management of general surgical cases and participation in a Consultant Surgeon of the Week (CSOW) rota, the department deals with the full range of benign and malignant oesophagogastric disease.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;All consultants are expected to participate in the on call rota (1 in 9 following appointment).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Countess of Chester Hospital is situated in a beautiful location on the outskirts of the historic Roman City of Chester. We are within easy access of Manchester Airport, North Wales and the Lake District. The Trust is committed to continued professional development, and to a culture of ongoing service improvement.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name Dale Vimalachandran&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title Clinical Lead for General Surgery/Consultant General and Colorectal Surgeon&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address dale.vimalachandran@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number01244 366089&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Mrs Nicola Eardley (Consultant General and Lower GI Surgeon) 01244 366089&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Mr Chris McFaul (Consultant General and Lower GI Surgeon) 01244 365262&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Mr Mike Johnson (Consultant General and Lower GI Surgeon) 01244 365516&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We would welcome further discussion with any interested candidates and would be pleased to arrange a visit to the Department for you.&lt;/p&gt;
